nguishes good and bad deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Hayyan reported: Ibn Mu\u2019adh, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cSincerity distinguishes good deeds from sins, just as milk is distinguished from filth and blood.\u201d And Sa\u2019id ibn Jubayr, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cSincerity is to not associate partners with Allah in one\u2019s religion, and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3855,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/27\/love-surah-ikhlaas-jannah\/","url_meta":{"origin":24325,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Love for Surat al-Ikhlas leads to Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 27, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, I love this chapter, 'Say: He is Allah, the One,'\" (112:1). The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cYour love for it will admit\u00a0you into Paradise.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 774 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to\u00a0Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42135,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/08\/22\/tawheed-reaches-arsh\/","url_meta":{"origin":24325,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Tawhid: It reaches the Throne if major sins avoided","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 22, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNever does a servant sincerely say, \u2018There is no God but Allah,\u2019 but that the gates of heaven open for it, even leading to the Throne itself, as long as he avoids major sins.\u201d Source: Sunan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26952,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/12\/30\/umar-ii-sincerity-take-care-dunya\/","url_meta":{"origin":24325,"position":3},"title":"Umar II on Akhirah: Set right your Hereafter, Allah will care for your world","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 30, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Dunya reported:\u00a0Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cTake care of your Hereafter and Allah will take care of your worldly life. Take care of your private life and Allah will take care of your public life.\u201d Source:\u00a0Kita\u0304b al-Ikhla\u0304s\u0323 50 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24323,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/02\/01\/ibn-al-mubarak-ikhlaas\/","url_meta":{"origin":24325,"position":4},"title":"Ibn Mubarak on Ikhlaas: Best deed is to be sincere to Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Dunya reported: Ibn al-Mubarak, may Allah have mercy on him, was asked, \u201cWhich deed is best?\u201d Ibn al-Mubarak said, \u201cSincerity to Allah.\u201d Source: al-Amr bil-Ma\u2019ru\u0304f li Ibn Abi\u0304 Dunya\u0304 71 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0631\u064e\u0643\u0650 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u00a0\u0633\u064f\u0626\u0650\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0641\u0652\u0636\u064e\u0644\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064f\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064f \u0644\u0650\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 71 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0631\u0648\u0641\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24375,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/02\/05\/ikhlas-pure-inward-outward\/","url_meta":{"origin":24325,"position":5},"title":"Mutarrif on Sincerity: True servants of Allah are pure inwardly, outwardly","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 5, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Sari reported: Mutarrif, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cVerily, when the inward state of the servant matches his public behavior, Allah says: This is my true servant.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li Hanna\u0304d Ibn al-Sari\u0304 530 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0631\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0637\u064e\u06